quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  71,1,"Indeed, We sent Noah to his people ˹saying to him˺, “Warn your people before a painful punishment comes to them.”"
  71,2,"Noah proclaimed, “O my people! I am truly sent to you with a clear warning"
  71,3,"worship Allah ˹alone˺, fear Him, and obey me"
  71,4,"He will forgive your sins, and delay your end until the appointed time. Indeed, when the time set by Allah comes, it cannot be delayed, if only you knew!”"
  71,5,"He cried, “My Lord! I have surely called my people day and night"
  71,6,but my calls only made them run farther away
  71,7,"And whenever I invite them to be forgiven by You, they press their fingers into their ears, cover themselves with their clothes, persist ˹in denial˺, and act very arrogantly"
  71,8,Then I certainly called them openly
  71,9,then I surely preached to them publicly and privately
  71,10,"saying, ‘Seek your Lord’s forgiveness, ˹for˺ He is truly Most Forgiving"
  71,11,He will shower you with abundant rain
  71,12,"supply you with wealth and children, and give you gardens as well as rivers"
  71,13,What is the matter with you that you are not in awe of the Majesty of Allah
  71,14,when He truly created you in stages ˹of development˺
  71,15,"Do you not see how Allah created seven heavens, one above the other"
  71,16,"placing the moon within them as a ˹reflected˺ light, and the sun as a ˹radiant˺ lamp"
  71,17,Allah ˹alone˺ caused you to grow from the earth like a plant
  71,18,"Then He will return you to it, and then simply bring you forth ˹again˺"
  71,19,And Allah ˹alone˺ spread out the earth for you
  71,20,to walk along its spacious pathways.’”